{"title_page": "Romin Madinov", "text_new": "{{Infobox officeholder\n | honorific_prefix   = \n | name               = Romin Madinov\n | native_name        = \u0420\u043e\u043c\u0438\u043d \u041c\u0430\u0434\u0438\u043d\u043e\u0432\n | image              = Romin Madinov.jpg\n | caption            = \n | office             = Member of the [[Mazhilis]]\n | term_start         = 1 December 1999\n | term_end           = 25 March 2016\n | office2            = Chairman of [[Agrarian Party of Kazakhstan|Agrarian Party]]\n | term_start2        = 6 January 1999\n | term_end2          = 22 November 2006\n | predecessor2       = Position established\n | successor2         = Position abolished\n | birth_date         = {{birth date and age|1961|10|22|df=y}} \n | birth_place        = [[Qzyltu]], [[Kazakh SSR]], [[Soviet Union]]\n | death_date         = \n | death_place        = \n | party              = [[Nur Otan]] (2006\u2212present)\n | otherparty         = [[Agrarian Party of Kazakhstan|Agrarian Party]] (1999\u22122006)<br>[[Otan (party)|Otan]] (2006)\n}}\n'''Romin Rizuly Madinov''' ({{lang-kk|\u0420\u043e\u043c\u0438\u043d \u0420\u0438\u0437\u04b1\u043b\u044b \u041c\u0430\u0434\u0438\u043d\u043e\u0432}}, ''Rom\u0131n R\u0131zuly Mad\u0131nov'') (born 22 October 1961) is a Kazakh politician who served as a member of the Mazhilis from 1999 to 2016 and was a Chairman of the [[Agrarian Party of Kazakhstan|Agrarian Party]] from 1999 until it was merged with the [[Otan (party)|Otan]] party in 2006.\n\n==Biography==\nBorn in the village of [[Qzyltu]] in the [[Kokshetau Region]] of [[Kazakh SSR]], Madinov graduated from the Omsk State University in 1988.\nIn the mid 1990s, Madinov founded the Agrocenter Company.<ref>http://kvnews.ru/archive/2005/jur13(685)/business/3398</ref>\n\nOn 6 January 1999, the Agrarian Party held it's congress for which Madinov became the chairman. It became registered on 16 March 1999 by the Ministry of Justice of Kazakhstan. In September 1999, Madinov was elected to the Mazhilis in the [[1999 Kazakh legislative election|1999 legislative election]], winning only 3 seats. On 28 July 2004, the Agrarian Party formed a [[Agrarian and Civic Union of Workers Bloc|bloc]] with the [[Civic Party of Kazakhstan|Civic Party]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://nomad.su/?a=3-200407290014|title=\u0410\u0433\u0440\u0430\u0440\u043d\u0430\u044f \u0438 \u0413\u0440\u0430\u0436\u0434\u0430\u043d\u0441\u043a\u0430\u044f \u043f\u0430\u0440\u0442\u0438\u0438 \u0441\u043e\u0433\u043b\u0430\u0441\u043e\u0432\u0430\u043b\u0438 \u0435\u0434\u0438\u043d\u044b\u0439 \u0441\u043f\u0438\u0441\u043e\u043a \u043a\u0430\u043d\u0434\u0438\u0434\u0430\u0442\u043e\u0432 \u043d\u0430 \u0432\u044b\u0431\u043e\u0440\u044b \u0432 \u041c\u0430\u0436\u0438\u043b\u0438\u0441 {{!}} \u041d\u043e\u043c\u0430\u0434 {{!}} 29.07.2004|website=nomad.su|access-date=2020-01-19}}</ref> Madinov led the bloc which won 11 seats in the [[2004 Kazakh legislative election|2004 election]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.cnn.com/WORLD/election.watch/asiapcf/kazakhstan3.html|title=CNN.com - World News: Election Watch|website=www.cnn.com|access-date=2020-01-19}}</ref>\n\nOn 22 November 2006, at the 7th All-Congress of the Agrarian Party, a decision was made to incorporate the party into [[Otan (party)|Otan]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rferl.org/a/1073642.html|title=Ruling Party Gets Even Bigger|website=RadioFreeEurope/RadioLiberty|language=en|access-date=2020-01-19}}</ref> In the beginning of 2007, Madinov was interviewed by Khabar television channel and said that President [[Nursultan Nazarbayev]] should be given the opportunity to rule as much as he wants. On 4 July 2007, at the XI Extraordinary Congress of Nur Otan, Madinov was elected to the bureau of the party\u2019s Political Council.\n\nIn the [[2007 Kazakh legislative election|2007 legislative election]], Madinov ran as a Nur Otan party candidate. The party won 88.41% of the vote and was the only one that  overcame the 7% threshold.\n\n==2009 lawsuit==\nOn 16 January 2009, a judge of the Medeu District Court of Almaty, Ruslan Suleymanov, ruled on a lawsuit by Madinov about infringing on his honor and dignity against the opposition newspaper Tasjargan and its journalist Almas Kusherbaev. According to the court\u2019s decision, the newspaper and its journalist were to pay 3 million tenge to Madinov who had requested 300 million tenge in the lawsuit, as well as publish a refutation of the article \u201cPoor Latifundist,\u201d which became the primary reason the trial.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://rus.azattyq.org/a/1370980.html|title=\u0413\u0430\u0437\u0435\u0442\u0430 \u201c\u0422\u0430\u0441\u0436\u0430\u0440\u0433\u0430\u043d\u201d \u0438 \u0435\u0435 \u0436\u0443\u0440\u043d\u0430\u043b\u0438\u0441\u0442 \u043e\u0431\u044f\u0437\u0430\u043d\u044b \u0432\u044b\u043f\u043b\u0430\u0442\u0438\u0442\u044c \u0442\u0440\u0438 \u043c\u0438\u043b\u043b\u0438\u043e\u043d\u0430 \u0442\u0435\u043d\u0433\u0435 \u043a\u043e\u043c\u043f\u0435\u043d\u0441\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0438 \u041c\u0430\u0434\u0438\u043d\u043e\u0432\u0443|website=\u0420\u0430\u0434\u0438\u043e \u0410\u0437\u0430\u0442\u0442\u044b\u043a|language=ru|access-date=2020-01-19}}</ref> The Almaty City Court's appeal on the newspaper and it's journalist not only cancel the decision of the district court, but also increased the amount of payment in favor of Madinov to 30 million tenge.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://vesti.kz/crime/1865/|title=\u0413\u0430\u0437\u0435\u0442\u0430 \"\u0422\u0430\u0441\u0436\u0430\u0440\u0433\u0430\u043d\" \u043e\u0441\u043f\u043e\u0440\u0438\u0442 \u0440\u0435\u0448\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0435 \u0441\u0443\u0434\u0430|website=Vesti.kz|language=ru|access-date=2020-01-19}}</ref> According to the advocates of the newspaper and the journalist, the content of the article was about the economic feasibility of raising the price of bread, and it was debatable, analytical in nature with the hypotheses and methods characteristic of this genre in order to draw attention to the problem in question, and not to Madinov\u2019s persona.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://rus.azattyq.org/a/Tashzrgan_newspaper/1499735.html|title=\u0413\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0434\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0439 \u0441\u0443\u0434 \u043d\u0435 \u0443\u043c\u0435\u043d\u044c\u0448\u0438\u043b \u0448\u0442\u0440\u0430\u0444 \u0441 \u043e\u043f\u043f\u043e\u0437\u0438\u0446\u0438\u043e\u043d\u043d\u043e\u0439 \u0433\u0430\u0437\u0435\u0442\u044b \u00ab\u0422\u0430\u0441\u0436\u0430\u0440\u0433\u0430\u043d\u00bb, \u0430 \u0443\u0432\u0435\u043b\u0438\u0447\u0438\u043b \u0432 10 \u0440\u0430\u0437|website=\u0420\u0430\u0434\u0438\u043e \u0410\u0437\u0430\u0442\u0442\u044b\u043a|language=ru|access-date=2020-01-19}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:1961 births]]\n[[Category:Members of the Mazhilis]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n\n\n{{Kazakhstan-politician-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox officeholder\n | honorific_prefix   = \n | name               = Romin Madinov\n | native_name        = \u0420\u043e\u043c\u0438\u043d \u041c\u0430\u0434\u0438\u043d\u043e\u0432\n | image              = Romin Madinov.jpg\n | caption            = \n | office             = Member of the [[Mazhilis]]\n | term_start         = 1 December 1999\n | term_end           = 25 March 2016\n | office2            = Chairman of [[Agrarian Party of Kazakhstan|Agrarian Party]]\n | term_start2        = 6 January 1999\n | term_end2          = 22 November 2006\n | predecessor2       = Position established\n | successor2         = Position abolished\n | birth_date         = {{birth date and age|1961|10|22|df=y}} \n | birth_place        = [[Qzyltu]], [[Kazakh SSR]], [[Soviet Union]]\n | death_date         = \n | death_place        = \n | party              = [[Nur Otan]] (2006\u2212present)\n | otherparty         = [[Agrarian Party of Kazakhstan|Agrarian Party]] (1999\u22122006)<br>[[Otan (party)|Otan]] (2006)\n}}\n'''Romin Rizuly Madinov''' ({{lang-kk|\u0420\u043e\u043c\u0438\u043d \u0420\u0438\u0437\u04b1\u043b\u044b \u041c\u0430\u0434\u0438\u043d\u043e\u0432}}, ''Rom\u0131n R\u0131zuly Mad\u0131nov'') (born 22 October 1961) is a Kazakh politician who served as a member of the Mazhilis from 1999 to 2016 and was a Chairman of the [[Agrarian Party of Kazakhstan|Agrarian Party]] from 1999 until it was merged with the [[Otan (party)|Otan]] party in 2006.\n\n==Biography==\nBorn in the village of [[Qzyltu]] in the [[Kokshetau Region]] of [[Kazakh SSR]], Madinov graduated from the Omsk State University in 1988.\nIn the mid 1990's, Madinov founded the Agrocenter Company.<ref>http://kvnews.ru/archive/2005/jur13(685)/business/3398</ref>\n\nOn 6 January 1999, the Agrarian Party held it's congress for which Madinov became the chairman. It became registered on 16 March 1999 by the Ministry of Justice of Kazakhstan. In September 1999, Madinov was elected to the Mazhilis in the [[1999 Kazakh legislative election|1999 legislative election]], winning only 3 seats. On 28 July 2004, the Agrarian Party formed a [[Agrarian and Civic Union of Workers Bloc|bloc]] with the [[Civic Party of Kazakhstan|Civic Party]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://nomad.su/?a=3-200407290014|title=\u0410\u0433\u0440\u0430\u0440\u043d\u0430\u044f \u0438 \u0413\u0440\u0430\u0436\u0434\u0430\u043d\u0441\u043a\u0430\u044f \u043f\u0430\u0440\u0442\u0438\u0438 \u0441\u043e\u0433\u043b\u0430\u0441\u043e\u0432\u0430\u043b\u0438 \u0435\u0434\u0438\u043d\u044b\u0439 \u0441\u043f\u0438\u0441\u043e\u043a \u043a\u0430\u043d\u0434\u0438\u0434\u0430\u0442\u043e\u0432 \u043d\u0430 \u0432\u044b\u0431\u043e\u0440\u044b \u0432 \u041c\u0430\u0436\u0438\u043b\u0438\u0441 {{!}} \u041d\u043e\u043c\u0430\u0434 {{!}} 29.07.2004|website=nomad.su|access-date=2020-01-19}}</ref> Madinov led the bloc which won 11 seats in the [[2004 Kazakh legislative election|2004 election]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.cnn.com/WORLD/election.watch/asiapcf/kazakhstan3.html|title=CNN.com - World News: Election Watch|website=www.cnn.com|access-date=2020-01-19}}</ref>\n\nOn 22 November 2006, at the 7th All-Congress of the Agrarian Party, a decision was made to incorporate the party into [[Otan (party)|Otan]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rferl.org/a/1073642.html|title=Ruling Party Gets Even Bigger|website=RadioFreeEurope/RadioLiberty|language=en|access-date=2020-01-19}}</ref> In the beginning of 2007, Madinov was interviewed by Khabar television channel and said that President [[Nursultan Nazarbayev]] should be given the opportunity to rule as much as he wants. On 4 July 2007, at the XI Extraordinary Congress of Nur Otan, Madinov was elected to the bureau of the party\u2019s Political Council.\n\nIn the [[2007 Kazakh legislative election|2007 legislative election]], Madinov ran as a Nur Otan party candidate. The party won 88.41% of the vote and was the only one that  overcame the 7% threshold.\n\n==2009 lawsuit==\nOn 16 January 2009, a judge of the Medeu District Court of Almaty, Ruslan Suleymanov, ruled on a lawsuit by Madinov about infringing on his honor and dignity against the opposition newspaper Tasjargan and its journalist Almas Kusherbaev. According to the court\u2019s decision, the newspaper and its journalist were to pay 3 million tenge to Madinov who had requested 300 million tenge in the lawsuit, as well as publish a refutation of the article \u201cPoor Latifundist,\u201d which became the primary reason the trial.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://rus.azattyq.org/a/1370980.html|title=\u0413\u0430\u0437\u0435\u0442\u0430 \u201c\u0422\u0430\u0441\u0436\u0430\u0440\u0433\u0430\u043d\u201d \u0438 \u0435\u0435 \u0436\u0443\u0440\u043d\u0430\u043b\u0438\u0441\u0442 \u043e\u0431\u044f\u0437\u0430\u043d\u044b \u0432\u044b\u043f\u043b\u0430\u0442\u0438\u0442\u044c \u0442\u0440\u0438 \u043c\u0438\u043b\u043b\u0438\u043e\u043d\u0430 \u0442\u0435\u043d\u0433\u0435 \u043a\u043e\u043c\u043f\u0435\u043d\u0441\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0438 \u041c\u0430\u0434\u0438\u043d\u043e\u0432\u0443|website=\u0420\u0430\u0434\u0438\u043e \u0410\u0437\u0430\u0442\u0442\u044b\u043a|language=ru|access-date=2020-01-19}}</ref> The Almaty City Court's appeal on the newspaper and it's journalist not only cancel the decision of the district court, but also increased the amount of payment in favor of Madinov to 30 million tenge.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://vesti.kz/crime/1865/|title=\u0413\u0430\u0437\u0435\u0442\u0430 \"\u0422\u0430\u0441\u0436\u0430\u0440\u0433\u0430\u043d\" \u043e\u0441\u043f\u043e\u0440\u0438\u0442 \u0440\u0435\u0448\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0435 \u0441\u0443\u0434\u0430|website=Vesti.kz|language=ru|access-date=2020-01-19}}</ref> According to the advocates of the newspaper and the journalist, the content of the article was about the economic feasibility of raising the price of bread, and it was debatable, analytical in nature with the hypotheses and methods characteristic of this genre in order to draw attention to the problem in question, and not to Madinov\u2019s persona.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://rus.azattyq.org/a/Tashzrgan_newspaper/1499735.html|title=\u0413\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0434\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0439 \u0441\u0443\u0434 \u043d\u0435 \u0443\u043c\u0435\u043d\u044c\u0448\u0438\u043b \u0448\u0442\u0440\u0430\u0444 \u0441 \u043e\u043f\u043f\u043e\u0437\u0438\u0446\u0438\u043e\u043d\u043d\u043e\u0439 \u0433\u0430\u0437\u0435\u0442\u044b \u00ab\u0422\u0430\u0441\u0436\u0430\u0440\u0433\u0430\u043d\u00bb, \u0430 \u0443\u0432\u0435\u043b\u0438\u0447\u0438\u043b \u0432 10 \u0440\u0430\u0437|website=\u0420\u0430\u0434\u0438\u043e \u0410\u0437\u0430\u0442\u0442\u044b\u043a|language=ru|access-date=2020-01-19}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:1961 births]]\n[[Category:Members of the Mazhilis]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n\n\n{{Kazakhstan-politician-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Alistair1978", "label": "safe", "comment": "typo (viaWP:JWB)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Romin_Madinov"}
{"title_page": "Malikayya Guttedar", "text_new": "{{Use Indian English|date=June 2019}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2019}}{{Infobox officeholder    |birth_date ={{birth_date and age|1956|5|13|df=y}} |birth_place =[[Solapur]]       |nationality =[[India]]n}} \n'''Malikaiah Venkaiah Guttedar''' is an Indian member of the [[Karnataka Legislative Assembly]], representing the town of [[Afzalpur]] in the district of [[Gulbarga]]. Ex Minister Government of Karnataka and senior leader from [[Gulbarga district|Gulbarga]] district He was a member of the [[Indian National Congress]] party but joined BJP<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://zeenews.india.com/india/with-month-to-go-for-karnataka-polls-6-time-congress-mla-malikayya-venkayya-guttedar-joins-bjp-2097893.html|title=With month to go for Karnataka polls, 6-time Congress MLA Malikayya Venkayya Guttedar joins BJP|date=2018-04-08|work=Zee News|access-date=2018-04-09|language=en}}</ref> on 9 April 2018.<ref>http://myneta.info/karnataka2013/candidate.php?candidate_id=434</ref> He recently lost against MY Patil in [[2018 Karnataka Legislative Elections]]\n\nOn 24 April 2017, a racing car driven by Guttedar's son went airborne, flipped over three times and crashed on a racing track near [[Virajpet]] with a passenger inside.<ref>{{cite news | url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/bengaluru/miraculous-escape-for-mla-guttedars-son-as-car-flips-crashes/articleshow/58352558.cms | title=Miraculous escape for MLA Guttedar's son as car flips, crashes | date=25 April 2017 | newspaper=The Times of India | accessdate=14 June 2019 }}</ref> Both racers were safe.\n\n== References ==\n<references />\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Guttedar, Malikayya Venkayya}}\n[[Category:Karnataka MLAs 2013\u20132018]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:Place of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:Indian National Congress politicians from Karnataka]]\n[[Category:People from Gulbarga district]]\n\n\n{{Karnataka-politician-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use Indian English|date=June 2019}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2019}}{{Infobox officeholder    |birth_date ={{birth_date and age|1956|5|13|df=y}} |birth_place =[[Solapur]]       |nationality =[[India]]n}} \n'''Malikaiah Venkaiah Guttedar''' is a Indian member of the [[Karnataka Legislative Assembly]], representing the town of [[Afzalpur]] in the district of [[Gulbarga]]. Ex Minister Government of Karnataka and senior leader from [[Gulbarga district|Gulbarga]] district He was a member of the [[Indian National Congress]] party but joined BJP<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://zeenews.india.com/india/with-month-to-go-for-karnataka-polls-6-time-congress-mla-malikayya-venkayya-guttedar-joins-bjp-2097893.html|title=With month to go for Karnataka polls, 6-time Congress MLA Malikayya Venkayya Guttedar joins BJP|date=2018-04-08|work=Zee News|access-date=2018-04-09|language=en}}</ref> on 9 April 2018.<ref>http://myneta.info/karnataka2013/candidate.php?candidate_id=434</ref> He recently lost against MY Patil in [[2018 Karnataka Legislative Elections]]\n\nOn 24 April 2017, a racing car driven by Guttedar's son went airborne, flipped over three times and crashed on a racing track near [[Virajpet]] with a passenger inside.<ref>{{cite news | url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/bengaluru/miraculous-escape-for-mla-guttedars-son-as-car-flips-crashes/articleshow/58352558.cms | title=Miraculous escape for MLA Guttedar's son as car flips, crashes | date=25 April 2017 | newspaper=The Times of India | accessdate=14 June 2019 }}</ref> Both racers were safe.\n\n== References ==\n<references />\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Guttedar, Malikayya Venkayya}}\n[[Category:Karnataka MLAs 2013\u20132018]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:Place of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:Indian National Congress politicians from Karnataka]]\n[[Category:People from Gulbarga district]]\n\n\n{{Karnataka-politician-s